<biogHist>
<abstract>A Children's Nursing Home provided accommodation in a private home for children under five years old.</abstract>
<p>Children's Nursing Homes were run by a woman who took care of the children in return for a fee usually paid by the mother. The mothers were usually single and placed their children in the Home so that they could earn a living to support them.</p>
<p>The first Homes were established under the <span style="font-style:italic">Infant Life Protection Act</span> 1907. Nurses from the Police Department inspected these Homes. In 1918, under the <span style="font-style:italic">Children of the State Act</span>, the Children of the State Department took over their management. The <span style="font-style:italic">Infants Welfare Act</span> of 1935 employed the term but its usage had disappeared by 1960 when the <span style="font-style:italic">Child Welfare Act</span> became law.</p>

</biogHist>
